news_text:
2025-05-21 19:15 ET - News Release
Mr. Gerard Bond reports
OCEANAGOLD RELEASES 2024 SUSTAINABILITY REPORT
Oceanagold Corp. has  published its annual sustainability report and related documents for the year ended Dec. 31, 2024.
Gerard Bond, president and chief executive officer of Oceanagold, said: "We made good progress on our sustainability commitments in 2024, consistent with our purpose of mining gold for a better future. Operating safely and responsibly is a strategic imperative for Oceanagold as we know that a comprehensive, integrated and company-wide approach to sustainability is fundamental to creating and protecting value for all our stakeholders."
Megan Saussey, chief sustainability officer of Oceanagold, said, "Two thousand twenty-four was a year of implementation of our updated three-year sustainability strategy, with a focus on strengthening our core responsible business practices and maintaining consistent performance across the business."
2024 sustainability performance outcomes:
Maintained an MSCI AA and leader rating;
Commenced implementation of its updated three-year sustainability strategy;
Developed and progressed safety improvement plans and embedded the investigation learnings across all sites following two fatalities during the year;
Achieved an 80-per-cent employee engagement score for its 2024 culture survey results, exceeding the global mining and metal benchmark by 8 per cent and demonstrating a strong level of connection to, and satisfaction with, working at Oceanagold;
Maintained its record of zero material environmental incidents;
Completed over 100 hectares of progressive rehabilitation of disturbed mine land to the agreed end use, over 30 per cent more land than what was disturbed in the year;
Conducted approximately 250 facilitated engagements with Iwi groups (Maori peoples), which groups have indicated an interest in the Waihi North project in New Zealand;
Spent over $193-million (U.S.) with local suppliers, paid $125-million (U.S.) in taxes and royalties to host governments, and contributed $11-million (U.S.) to social investments and community partnerships;
Completed portfolio-level climate change transition and physical climate scenario and risk analysis;
Met 70 per cent of company-wide water needs through reused or recycled water.
About Oceanagold 

Corp.
Oceanagold is a growing intermediate gold and copper producer committed to safely and responsibly maximizing the generation of free cash flow from its operations and delivering strong returns for its shareholders. It has a portfolio of four operating mines: the Haile gold mine in the United States, the Didipio mine in the Philippines, and the Macraes and Waihi operations in New Zealand.
